why climate adaptation has implications for how we understand the past and the continued human settlement of a place. Such understandings become particularly apparent not only through experts’ and ordinary citizens’ disputes over resources but in their attention to the ethical practice of technoscience over time. Approaching climate adaptation this way, Vaughn exposes the generative openings as well as gaps in racial thinking for theorizing climate action, environmental justice, and, more broadly, future life on a warming planet.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aClimate change mitigationzGuyana. 0aClimatic changeszGuyana. 0aEnvironmental educationzGuyana. 0aFloodszGuyana. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022725?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022725/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-